        "Several features of the fitted model are worth noting. The level smoothing parameter $\\alpha$ reflects how quickly the model updates its estimate of the current level in response to new observations. The damping parameter $\\phi$ (close to 1 but below it) indicates modest damping — the model retains most of the trend momentum but expects it to fade somewhat over the forecast horizon. The seasonal parameter $\\gamma$ controls how much the model learns about seasonal factors from each new year of data; a small value means the estimated seasonal pattern changes slowly, which is appropriate for a series whose seasonal structure has been stable for decades.\n",
